<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="author" content="@REPOSITORY_AUTHOR@">
  <meta name="description" content="Documentation about generated flatpak ostree repository in github pages.">
  <meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark">
  <title>Flatpak Repository Usage</title>
</head>

<body>
  <main>
    <div id="root">
      <h1 class="title">Flatpak repository for @REPOSITORY_URL@</h1>
      <div>
        <h2 class="content" id="usage">Usage:</h2>
        <p>You can run those commands to add this repository to your flatpak and install:</p>
        <pre>
          <code>
            flatpak remote-add liteloader @PAGES_URL@/com.qq.QQ.flatpakrepo
            flatpak install com.qq.QQ # Select the one from `liteloader` remote if prompted
          </code>
        </pre>
        <p>Or you can download built flatpak bundles from <a
            href="@REPOSITORY_URL@/actions/workflows/release.yaml?query=is%3Asuccess">Github Action Artifacts</a>
          and install them manually:</p>
        <pre>
          <code>
            flatpak install /path/to/bundle.flatpak
          </code>
        </pre>
        <p>Please note that manually installing cannot provide automatical updates.
          You have to update them manually by downloading new version and install again.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</body>

</html>